// LLM-as-judge eval dataset.
// One JSON object per line. `//` comment lines are skipped by the loader.
//
// Each row pairs a natural-language prompt (sent to the SUT LLM agent) with
// a reference fetch that the harness performs directly via Voli's analytics
// layer (no LLM in the loop on the reference side). A separate judge LLM
// then grades whether the SUT's answer matches the reference data within
// the per-row rubric_hint tolerance.
//
// All reference tools are deterministic Polygon-backed analytics:
//   compute_atm_iv_term_structure  -> front_iv, next_iv, atm_strike, expiries
//   compute_skew_slope             -> skew_slope, expiry, atm_strike
//   get_atm_greeks                 -> atm.iv/delta/gamma/theta/vega
//
// Categories: 10 term_structure, 10 skew, 10 greeks = 30 total.
//
// === term_structure (10) ===================================================
{"id": "ts_001", "category": "term_structure", "prompt": "What's NVDA's ATM IV for this Friday vs next?", "reference_tool": "compute_atm_iv_term_structure", "reference_args": {"ticker": "NVDA"}, "rubric_hint": "Front IV, next IV, and ATM strike must match the reference within 0.5 vol points (0.005) and $1 of strike."}
